a teapot: https://git.sr.ht/~rabbits/uxnmin/tree/master/item/src/uxnmin.c
a teapot: instead of having a stack structure, instead I've broken it down into an array of pointers
a teapot: and an array of data
a teapot: so instead of branching, which limits of bitwise operations to being two steps, I can do ptr[return_mode]
a teapot: which simplifies a lot of the core operators(push/pop) and makes some other things faster too
a teapot: compare with old POP2
a teapot: #define PO2(o) { PO1(o) if(_r) o |= DEC(rst) << 8; else o |= DEC(wst) << 8; }
a teapot: new POP2
a teapot: #define PO2(o) { o = DEC(_r) | DEC(_r) << 8; }
a teapot: I'll implement the change to uxn11
chloe: oh thats really smart!, i should optimize that in uxn-pebble aswell
