a teapot: there isn't much to it, computation is done with a single operation, mulitply
a teapot: do you know how multiplying a number by a fraction, is essentially subtracting prime factors below, and adding above
a teapot: 18 * 2/3, is the same as saying take a 3 out, and put a 2 instead
a teapot: 18(2*3*3) * 2/3 -> 18(-r3, +r2) -> 12(2*2*3)
a teapot: if you remove the numbers and user names, like colors of marbles red(2), green(3), blue(5)
a teapot: your program becomes a series of rewrite rules, which are essentially fractions
a teapot: take a red, put two greens, 3*3/2
a teapot: any bag of marbles that you multiply with 9/3 will add 2 green marbles, for every red ones.
a teapot: from this single operation(multiply) you can build any program imaginable.
