mostlypat: d_m: how come you are upgrading from source? sorry if thats a very personal question ;)
mostlypat: ive toyed multiple times with the idea of making a KISS-linux thing, but the compilation times always disuaded me
d_m: so i have these 32-bit systems...
d_m: some of which run NetBSD.
d_m: NetBSD is (unfortunately) small enough that the i386 port doesn't have full build coverage
d_m: so there are some packages that are in pkgsrc but which don't have a binary package to install. so you have to build them
d_m: (and this can quickly get out of control with transitive deps)
d_m: it's one of my least favorite things about rust; everything seems to need bleeding edge rustc
d_m: which often pulls in bleeding edge LLVM
mostlypat: ahh, that makes sense. its all part of Big Bit's agenda to crush 32-bits :(
d_m: heh. it does feel like that sometimes
d_m: seeing system requirements creeping up and up, etc.
d_m: my (heterodox) opinion is that we should be able to run our operating systems on an  esp32
