d_m: one idea would be to write up and implement the muxn idea i had for low power system
d_m: i.e. basically varvara but with less mem, smaller stacks, and/or fewer screen layers
d_m: waso amisi, excited to see what you come up with
chloe: d_m, that is sorta what i did for the pebble uxn port
d_m: nice! my idea is basically just how to describe the limits
d_m: so mxun842 is basically "normal" varvara.
chloe: the constraints i had were: only 1 screen layer, colours are defined by the emulator and not the application, some watches can only handle 0xedf ammount of memory
d_m: mxun-abc means 2^a pages of memory, 16*2^b bytes of stack, and c screen layers
d_m: so it sounds like pebble would be muxn341 according to muxn spec
d_m: 2048 bytes of memory (mirrored 32x), normal stacks (256 bytes), only 1 screen layer
chloe: i was just about to say that
d_m: the other changes are just allowing emulator to decide to crash on stack overflow, to detect incompatibilities
d_m: and a few other things like that
d_m: this might be an argument against smaller stacks
d_m: but on constrained systems feels bad to "waste" 512 bytes on wst/rst
d_m: when 32 or 64 byte stacks are likely perfectly ok
chloe: i feel like you could get away with only having the return stack be halfsized
d_m: hm, maybe, but lack of symmetry bugs me ;)
d_m: the "goal" here is to make it feasible to write a good varvara emulator for z80, 6502, etc.
d_m: without requiring those systems to have extra memory banks and >64k of memory
d_m: (also gives an elegant way to write varvara-in-varvara without requiring extra pages)
chloe: would there be a way for the rom to see what capabilities the emulator offers?
chloe: like a device of somesorts?
waso amisi: chloe, will do!
d_m: chloe assuming the emulator correctly masks/mirrors addresses, you can detect mem size
d_m: and you can use stack underflow + system device to detect stack size
d_m: i plan to provide these autodetection snippets
d_m: i don't know of a good way to do this for the screen besides a new device
d_m: honestly i wish the existing emulator had more of thse capabilities!
d_m: anyway that's something i'll have to figure out
